In BLE, calls to BluetoothGatt&#39;s `readCharacteristic()` and `writeCharacteristic()` are not blocking. They return `true` if the operation was initiated successfully.

When the operation is complete, you will receive the results in your implementation of BluetoothGattCallback&#39;s `onCharacteristicRead()` and `onCharacteristicWrite()`

If you need to display some results on your UI, run these operation in the UI thread:

    getActivity().runOnUiThread(new Runnable() {

                @Override
                public void run() {
                    // UI operations ...
                }
            });

For more infos on `writeCharacteristic()`
https://developer.android.com/reference/android/bluetooth/BluetoothGatt.html#writeCharacteristic(android.bluetooth.BluetoothGattCharacteristic)

